text: Peschany () is a rural locality (a village) in Bulgakovsky Selsoviet, Ufimsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 181 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 26 km from Ufa, 6 km from Bulgakovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Ufimsky District
title: Peschany, Ufimsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
